      Most Vernal storage facilities look similar at first glance. The differences that matter — construction type, pest protection, access hours, who you call when something's wrong — only become clear when you dig in.
    </p>

    <div class="features-grid" style="max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto;">

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔩</div>
        <h3>Construction: Steel vs. Wood</h3>
        <p>Fort Knox uses Cor-Ten steel shipping containers — cargo grade, fully sealed, no wood framing anywhere. Most Vernal storage facilities use wood-frame construction with thin metal siding. The difference matters most when mice are looking for a way in — and they always are.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🐭</div>
        <h3>Rodent Protection: Sealed vs. Exposed</h3>
        <p>Wood-frame storage units have floor gaps, wall joints, and framing that rodents can chew through. Fort Knox containers have no wood, no gaps, and no entry points. This is not a minor difference in the Uintah Basin — rodent damage to stored belongings is a real, recurring problem that steel eliminates entirely.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">⏰</div>
        <h3>Access Hours: 24/7 vs. Restricted</h3>
        <p>Many Vernal storage facilities restrict gate access to business hours or set windows. Fort Knox has no access restrictions — your personal gate code works at midnight, 4am, or any hour between. For oilfield workers and anyone with a non-standard schedule, this is not a small thing.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">💰</div>
        <h3>Fees: Flat Rate vs. Hidden Costs</h3>
        <p>Fort Knox charges $130/month for a 20ft container and $230/month for a 40ft. No deposit, no admin fee, no move-in charge. Some Vernal competitors require first month, last month, and a security deposit upfront — three times the monthly rate before you've stored a single box.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔥</div>
        <h3>Fire Detection: Active vs. None</h3>
        <p>Fort Knox has an active fire detection system monitoring the entire facility at no additional cost. Many budget storage options in Vernal have no fire detection. When you're storing valuable tools, equipment, or irreplaceable belongings, fire detection is not optional.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📞</div>
        <h3>Who You Call: Owner vs. Call Center</h3>
        <p>Call Fort Knox at 435-828-7710 and reach James Richards — the owner, a Vernal local, available 24/7. Call a national chain and reach a call center. If you have an issue at 2am, the difference between a local owner who picks up and a ticket number is not abstract.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

